{
  "stem": "9730.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember one morning, we were quartered in a-- in a very large building.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You might almost call it a mansion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We would often find quarters like that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it had a courtyard in which our mess had been set up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I came down for breakfast.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I see that on the other side of the courtyard, somebody is walking toward me, a big, burly man, who could-- could be an officer, and surrounded by-- by a group of people who turned out to be liberated [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] soldiers of other armies, Russians, French, Poles.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had-- they were carrying guns of every conceivable make that they had apparently captured.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had three German prisoners in tow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this man walked up to me and said, here, I got a few Krauts for you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They're-- they're awfully glad to be-- that the war is over for them, and you won't have any trouble with them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I would go through my normal routine, because I always had to establish who had captured them and where they had been captured, because that had some bearing on-- you know, on the lines that we were trying to determine where some of these people were.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I-- so this was-- I was stationed [INAUDIBLE] in a town called Maintenon, and-- about 20, 25 miles outside of Paris.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I got to the point of where I said, and where did you capture those?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, well, they were on the railroad tracks in Rambouillet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but they didn't put up much of a fight.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I could see, here was this-- this conglomerate of people, a soldier from every army and all these weapons, strange weapons.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
